<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Thorny" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Thorny,</orth> full of thorns, or pricking like thorns; properly and metaphorically: <cit><quote>t. brambles,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 629" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 629</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>t. hedgehogs,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the t. point of bare distress,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.94" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a t. wood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 59.</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.2.174" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 2, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 67</bibl>. <cit><quote>the sharp t. points of my alleged reasons,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.224" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 224</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the steep and t. way to heaven,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 48</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a --er piece of ground,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 153</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>